article.description: — Kyrese Mullen scored 25 points as Hampton beat Mid-Atlantic Christian 109-46 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Mullen puts up 25 in Hampton's 109-46 victory over Mid-Atlantic Christian
article.linkText: Mullen puts up 25 in Hampton's 109-46 victory over Mid-Atlantic Christian
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. -- — Kyrese Mullen scored 25 points as Hampton beat Mid-Atlantic Christian 109-46 on Thursday night. Mullen added 18 rebounds and three steals for the Pirates (1-1). Tedrick Wilcox Jr. scored 16 points and added eight rebounds. Daniel Banister was 7 of 12 shooting and 2 of 3 from the free throw line to finish with 16 points. Lancelot Maurer led the way for the Mustangs with 12 points. Noah Richardson-Keys added nine points and three steals for Mid-Atlantic Christian. Joshua Tyler also had seven points. NEXT UP Hampton's next game is Monday against Norfolk State on the road, and Mid-Atlantic Christian visits North Carolina Central on Tuesday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
